# Monorepo core

Read `AGENTS.md` before non-trivial changes.

## Package boundaries

- `packages/game-engine` — authoritative gameplay transitions; deterministic RNG only in `rng.ts`
- `packages/shared` — types, `cards.json`, stat/resource helpers
- `apps/web` — Next.js client; Zustand calls engine, never invents rules
- `packages/ui` — legacy; do not add new features here

Dependency direction: `web → game-engine → shared`. Never import `apps/web` from packages.

## Scope discipline

- One primary goal per session; state in-scope / out-of-scope files
- Prefer ≤5 files for bug fixes; split large work across tasks
- No drive-by refactors, no unrelated formatting sweeps
- Do not commit or push unless the user explicitly asks

## Verification

Before claiming done:

```bash
npm run build
npm run lint
```

After `apps/web`-only UI changes: `cd apps/web && npm run build`

## Style

- TypeScript strict, single quotes
- Avoid new comments unless business logic is non-obvious
- Minimal diff; match existing patterns in the touched file
